  "original_title": "\u0d9c\u0dcf\u0dbd\u0dd4 \u0d9a\u0ddc\u0da7\u0dd4\u0db4\u0dc0\u0dd4\u0dbb \u0db8\u0dad \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0ddd\u0db0\u0dad\u0dcf\u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca\u0da7 \u0db6\u0dcf\u0db0\u0dcf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Protesters obstruct the Galle Fort",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "A group of civil society activists staged a protest on the Galle Fort today (30) demanding the immediate removal of the current government, including the President, in the face of the current situation in the country.",
        "The protesters said that they tried to tear down the posters with their hands. Mr. G.H.Ajith Kumara, a former member of parliament and lawyer, said that the Galle Fort Wall is a place that any person can freely access and neither the police nor the army have the right to obstruct the expression of a person's opinion. The Sri Lanka Bar Association has also been informed about this."
      ],
